element.data: Investigation of serum lipids is indicated in those with coronary and other arterial disease, especially in patients younger than 40 years of age, and in those with family history of atherosclerosis or of hyperlipidemia. Also important in patients with xanthomas, hypothyroidism, nephrosis, renal failure, obesity, diabetes mellitus, alcoholism, primary biliary cirrhosis, and other types of cholestasis.
Collection Instructions: 1. Fasting overnight (12 hours). 2. Patient must not consume any alcohol for 24 hours before the specimen is drawn.
